data.title: Dr Philipp Eduard Anton von Lenard (1862
data.meta_description: Nobel Prize in Physics Recipient.   Philipp Lenard, a Hungarian-born German physicist, was known for his research on cathode rays, which led him to be the 1905 Nobel Prize in Physics recipient.
